text: Edna Doré, née Gorring,"DORÉ, Alexander ", Film and Tv database. URL last accessed on 2006-12-15 (31 May 1921 – 11 April 2014) was a British actress. Doré was known for her bit-part roles in situation comedies. She is mostly known for playing the character of Mo Butcher in the BBC soap opera EastEnders (1988–1990). She was born in Bromley, Kent, England. Doré died from emphysema at her Sussex, England home, aged 92. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1921 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Actors from Kent Category:Deaths from emphysema Category:Disease-related deaths in Sussex Category:English television actors Category:People from Bromley
